result.execSummary:
The defendant Debra A Schubert was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Debra A Schubert is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Debra A Schubert was found guilty of Election Fraud-Fraud/Nomination Certif., a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 12.13(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing hearing on February 6, 2017 at 11:00 am.

10:13 a.m.  Michael J. Balskus, Special Prosecutor appears in court.  Defendant, Debra Schubert appears in court along with attorney Wendy Patrickus.

Statement by Special Prosecutor Michael J. Balskus regarding joint recommendation.  Defense is requesting separate sentencing date.  Attorney Patrickus concurs.  

Court questions defendant.  Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  

Court accepts plea and finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 as charged and orders count 2 and count 3 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered today.   Sentencing is scheduled for Feb. 6, 2017 at 11:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 10:26 a.m.
